PODCAST HTML ENTITY DECODING FIX:

ISSUE: Episode descriptions showed HTML entities like &quot;×—×•×¤×¨×™× ×‘×™× ×”&quot; instead of clean Hebrew text.

SOLUTION: Added HTML entity decoding in rssParser.ts:

```typescript
// Helper function to decode HTML entities
function decodeHtmlEntities(text: string): string {
  const textArea = document.createElement('textarea');
  textArea.innerHTML = text;
  return textArea.value;
}
```

IMPLEMENTATION:
- Applied decoding to both episode titles and excerpts
- Used browser's native HTML parsing for reliable entity conversion
- Fixed display of quotes, apostrophes, and other special characters
- Ensured clean Hebrew text throughout the podcast interface

RESULT: Episode descriptions now display as clean Hebrew: "×—×•×¤×¨×™× ×‘×™× ×”" instead of "&quot;×—×•×¤×¨×™× ×‘×™× ×”&quot;"
